## Get Into Command Mission
The main idea of finding the flag is intense Forensics Skills and Cryptography Skills.

##### There are many stages in the challenge where there is probability to get stuck. Even I took much time.

#### Step-1:
After I downloaded `program.exe` and read the description 
```
Note: You do NOT need a specific operating system to solve this question.
```

#### Step-2:
So I tried to do `strings program.exe >> Dump.txt`

#### Step-3:
So, I checked for `ALDI` in it. I got this whole dump in it: [I got the idea because `cat Dump.txt | grep ALDI` gave `ALDI` output. So, there was something to build on]

```
ALDI
data:image/-
png;base64,
```
#### Step-4:
So, I directly converted this dump to image [here](https://codebeautify.org/base64-to-image-converter).
I got the flag there.

<img src="Flag.png">

#### Step-5:
Finally, the flag becomes: 
`Arm0uR_pPTi4`


_Sequentially this challenge might look easy, but I got stuck with program.exe in strings. Nobody generally does that_
